<s> One can not blame the project members for following Microsoft's example and requiring "normal" users to have write and delete access to program and administrator directories, but I would prefer to be able to separate program, data, and auxiliary files and to be able to assign rights to specific groups of users or groups of users.  </s>
<s> Therefore, I suggest that Amaya use a central .ini  </s>
<s> file for those parameters which the must be centrally set and for those parameters which the administrator wishes to centrally determine (i.e., override of locally set parameters).  </s>
<s> In addition, I suggest either a list paths to the user directories in the central .ini  </s>
